1 olive oil
20 g plant-based butter
1 packet basmati rice
1 courgette
1 bag baby broccoli
½ packet firm tofu
1 tbs plain flour
1 tsp soy sauce
½ packet tomato paste
1 box coconut milk
1 bag herbs
1 packet Crushed Peanuts
2 clove garlic
1.5 cup water (for the rice)
1 bunch Asian Greens
1 drizzle water (for the veggies)
1 sachet Sri Lankan spice blend
1 sachet curry powder
1 pinch sugar

Finely chop garlic. In a medium saucepan,
heat the plant-based butter with a dash of olive
oil over medium heat. Cook garlic until fragrant,
1-2 minutes. Add basmati rice, the water (for
the rice) and a pinch of salt, stir, then bring to
the boil. Reduce heat to low and cover with a lid.
Cook for 10 minutes, then remove from heat and
keep covered until rice is tender and the water is
absorbed, 10 minutes.

TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so
don't peek!

While the rice is cooking, thinly slice courgette
into half-moons. Trim baby broccoli. Roughly
chop Asian greens. Pat firm tofu (see ingredients)
dry and cut into 1cm chunks. In a shallow bowl,
combine the plain flour, curry powder and a
pinch of sugar and salt. Add tofu and gently toss
to coat.

Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat
with enough olive oil to cover the base of the pan.
Cook tofu, tossing occasionally, until browned and
warmed through, 3-4 minutes. Transfer to a paper
towel-lined plate.

Wipe out frying pan and return to medium-high
heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook courgette and
baby broccoli, tossing, until tender, 4-5 minutes.
Add Asian greens and cook until wilted,
1-2 minutes. Add a drizzle of the soy sauce and
water (for the veggies), then transfer to a bowl
and cover to keep warm.

TIP: Add a dash of water to the pan to help speed up
the cooking process.

Wipe out frying pan and return to medium heat
with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook Sri Lankan spice
blend and tomato paste (see ingredients), stirring,
until fragrant, 1 minute. Add coconut milk and
simmer until slightly thickened, 1-2 minutes.
Remove from the heat.

Divide garlic rice between bowls. Top with soy
veggies and crispy tofu. Pour over Sri Lankan
coconut sauce. Tear over herbs. Garnish with
crushed peanuts.